--- @target: between
Valida se `value` esta no intervalo fechado `[min, max]`.

**Sintaxe**
`func between(value: int, min: int, max: int) -> bool`
---
--- @target: positive
Valida inteiro positivo.

**Sintaxe**
`func positive(value: int) -> bool`
---
--- @target: non_negative
Valida inteiro maior ou igual a zero.

**Sintaxe**
`func non_negative(value: int) -> bool`
---
--- @target: negative
Valida inteiro negativo.

**Sintaxe**
`func negative(value: int) -> bool`
---
--- @target: non_zero
Valida inteiro diferente de zero.

**Sintaxe**
`func non_zero(value: int) -> bool`
---
--- @target: one_of
Valida se `value` pertence a `candidates`.

**Sintaxe**
`func one_of(value: int, candidates: list<int>) -> bool`
---
--- @target: not_empty
Valida texto nao vazio.

**Sintaxe**
`func not_empty(value: text) -> bool`
---
--- @target: min_length
Valida tamanho minimo de texto.

**Sintaxe**
`func min_length(value: text, min: int) -> bool`
---
--- @target: max_length
Valida tamanho maximo de texto.

**Sintaxe**
`func max_length(value: text, max: int) -> bool`
---
--- @target: length_between
Valida faixa de tamanho de texto.

**Sintaxe**
`func length_between(value: text, min: int, max: int) -> bool`
---
--- @target: no_whitespace
Valida ausencia de whitespace ASCII (`space`, `tab`, `\n`, `\r`).

**Sintaxe**
`func no_whitespace(value: text) -> bool`
---
--- @target: has_whitespace
Valida presenca de ao menos um whitespace ASCII.

**Sintaxe**
`func has_whitespace(value: text) -> bool`
---
